<HEADLINE>
<P>
MANLEY'S LIFETIME BAN IS MESSAGE TO YOUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Why does a gifted athlete such as Dexter Manley give it all up for drugs? One 
of the great talents of professional football, who admitted he was illiterate 
and sought help to improve himself, he commanded a fine salary, did local 
television work and had a solid future once his playing days were over. 
</P>
<P>
If there's a lesson to be learned from this sad ending to the career of Dexter 
Manley, maybe, just maybe, the youth of America will take heed and listen and 
learn -- Don't Do Drugs. 
</P>
<P>
PETER M. CAVALLO, Port Hueneme 
</P>
</TEXT>
