<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WOOTTON'S FREE THROWS HELP UCLA WIN, 73-70 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior guard Michele Wootton made two free throws in the final seconds to 
clinch UCLA's 73-70 victory over Eastern Illinois Friday night at Pauley 
Pavilion in the season opener for both teams. 
</P>
<P>
The Panthers outscored the Bruins, 16-2, to pull to within 63-60. Then, after 
the teams exchanged baskets, Wooton secured the win with her free throws. 
</P>
<P>
Center Molly Tideback led the Bruins with 23 points on 11-of-22 shooting. 
Reserve center Sheri Bouldin had 10 points and led both teams with 11 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore guard Barb Perkes led the Panthers with 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
CS Long Beach 94, Eastern Washington 61 -- Junior forward Lisa Reslock came off 
the bench to score 17 points and get 12 rebounds, both career highs, to lead 
the 49ers to a first-round victory in the Kansas State tournament at Manhattan, 
Kan. 
</P>
<P>
The taller 49ers dominated the boards, outrebounding Eastern Washington, 69-39. 
Center Angelique Lee had 12. 
</P>
<P>
Center Missy Chubb led Eastern Washington with 21 points. 
</P>
<P>
The 49ers will play Maryland. The Lady Terps beat Kansas State in the other 
first-round game, 74-66. 
</P>
</TEXT>
