<P>
Robert F. Erburu, chairman and chief executive of Times Mirror Co., has been 
named chairman of the Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco for 1990. The 
central bank's board of governors in Washington also appointed Erburu to a 
second three-year term as a director. Erburu has served as chairman for two 
years. Carolyn S. Chambers, president and chief executive of Chambers 
Communications Corp. of Eugene, Ore., was named deputy chairman. Times Mirror 
Co. is a Los Angeles-based media and information company. It publishes the Los 
Angeles Times. 
</P>
