<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SADDLEBACK COMES BACK IN SECOND HALF FOR VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saddleback College rallied in the second half to defeat Grossmont, 102-98, in 
the opening round of the four-team Saddleback men's basketball tournament 
Friday at Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
Charles Lockard led Saddleback with 27 points. Sophomore forward Terrell Malone 
added 25 points and 10 rebounds for Saddleback, which trailed at halftime, 
50-47. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Thompson had 13 points and 10 rebounds for the Gauchos (1-2). 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback plays Pasadena tonight at 7:30 in the championship game. Pasadena 
defeated Moorpark, 96-83, in the other game. Moorpark plays Grossmont at 5:30 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
In the College of the Desert men's tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago 94, Long Beach 72 -- Matt Lien scored 25 points to lead Rancho 
Santiago in the first round. Lien, a 6-foot-9 forward from Whittier Christian, 
has signed a national letter of intend to play at California. LaVern Broadnax 
added 16, Gene Altamirano and Corie Blount 15 each for Rancho Santiago (5-0), 
which led, 60-43, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
