<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PETITION DRIVE TARGETS RESIDENTIAL 
DEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Azusa First, a group of residents opposed to construction of 67 multifamily 
units on land next to the Azusa Greens Country Club, has begun a petition drive 
that could force the City Council to repeal decisions allowing the project or 
put the issue on the ballot. 
</P>
<P>
At its Nov. 6 meeting, the council voted to change the zoning on the 8.4-acre 
parcel from water conservation to multifamily residential. It also amended the 
General Plan and approved the design and tentative tract map proposed by D 
&amp; D development and developer Johnny Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
If the group is able to gather 1,413 signatures of registered voters by Dec. 6, 
the council would have to either repeal the decisions or put them on the April 
ballot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
