<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 BOYS HELD IN VANDALISM AT SCHOOL IN 
PALMDALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two boys were in custody Friday on suspicion of causing at least $67,000 in 
damage in a vandalism spree at a public elementary school in Palmdale, the Los 
Angeles County Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
Among the vandalized equipment were 15 IBM computer terminals and a computer 
mainframe that sustained $47,000 in damage when an automatic fire-extinguishing 
system was activated, sending fire-retardant foam into classrooms, officials 
said. Other damage included pried-open doors and ripped screens. 
</P>
<P>
The boys, 12 and 15, were being detained at the sheriff's Antelope Valley 
station on suspicion of felony vandalism, Lt. Dave Collin said. The boys, who 
are not students at the school, were noticed nearby shortly after deputies 
discovered the damage at Sumac Elementary School, in the 4000 block of East 
Avenue P-8, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
