<TEXT>
<P>
A baby boy found wrapped in a garbage bag on a snowy sidewalk began recovering 
from hypothermia Friday. The baby, estimated at 2 hours old, was dumped 
Thursday in a stack of garbage on a snowy curb outside an apartment building. 
</P>
<P>
The newborn's temperature dropped well below normal and did not register on a 
thermometer, a doctor said. A few more hours on the freezing sidewalk would 
have been fatal, he said. 
