NEWSWIRE: FALCON ROOKIE DIES IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ralph Norwood, a rookie tackle for the Atlanta Falcons, was killed in an 
automobile accident Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Norwood's car was found near a shopping mall eight miles south of the Falcon 
training complex in Suwanee, Ga. According to police, Norwood's car crossed 
into the oncoming lane, went 40 feet down a slight embankment and slammed into 
a tree. 
</P>
<P>
Roger DeWitt said Norwood, 23, was alone in the car. He apparently died of 
massive head and chest injuries. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot-7, 285-pound Norwood saw action in all 11 Atlanta games this season, 
starting once when veteran Mike Kenn was sidelined because of an injury. 
Norwood, a New Orleans native, is survived by his parents, three sisters, two 
brothers and a daughter, 2. 
