<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
European Takeover Plans: The European Community Commission said it plans to 
propose new measures early next year to make corporate takeovers in the 
12-nation trade bloc easier. The commission said in a statement that takeover 
bids faced formidable legal obstacles in many member countries, but such 
roadblocks could be overcome by new measures and the application of current EC 
legislation. The commission said it wants, among other things, to strengthen 
the voting rights of shareholders and force bidders to outline their plans to 
target companies and their employees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
