ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; 
</P>
<P>
DEPARTMENT TO OFFER CHRISTMAS PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two programs are scheduled by the Community Services Department for the holiday 
vacation season. 
</P>
<P>
Starting at 4:15 p.m. Monday, a three-week class titled "Visions of Sugarplums" 
teaches the art of making gingerbread men, stenciled tree ornaments and other 
goodies. The registration fee is $26 in addition to a $15 supply fee. 
</P>
<P>
From 6:30 p.m. to 9 p.m. Dec. 7, a one-day workshop called "Bake With Mom" is 
offered for parents and children ages 6 or older. The registration is $16, and 
there is a $10 supply fee. 
</P>
<P>
To sign up, call (714) 493-5911. 
</P>
